ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Date script was run
time script was started
Time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
Whether script was completed
Notes: 0 = Script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 1 = Script was completed (all conditions run)

ElementDescription: Task version
Amount participant owns in dollars
Counts how many times participant has bet on 1 specific dice face
Counts how many times participant has bet on 2 possible dice faces
Counts how many times participant has bet on 3 possible dice faces
Counts how many times participant has bet on 4 possible dice faces
Counts how many times participants selected a safe bet (bets on 3 or 4 dice faces)
Counts how many times participants selected a risky bet (bets on 1 or 2 dice faces)
Reflects the number of safe (bets on 3 or 4 numbers) vs. risky (bets on 1 or 2 numbers) choices. It is computed as number of safe bets minus number of risky bets.
Adds the number of winning bets
Adds the number of losing bets
